// DOM
// Document Object Model

// DOM is a programming interface for HTML and XML documents. 
// It represents the page so that programs can change the document structure, style, and content. 
// The DOM represents the document as a tree of nodes, where each node is an object representing a part of the document.

// DOM Basics

// HTML
<html>
    <head>
        <title>DOM Basics</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h1>DOM Basics</h1>
        <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
        <button id="myButton">Click me</button>
    </body>
</html>

// DOM Tree representation
// Document
// ├── html
// │   ├── head
// │   │   └── title
// │   └── body
// │       ├── h1
// │       ├── p
// │       └── button

// Every element in the HTML document is represented as a node in the DOM tree.
// The DOM allows us to access and manipulate these nodes using JavaScript.
// Allows dynamic UI updates, event handling, and more.